Pair these guardrails with investment in modernization—cleaner energy, efficiency, and resilient infrastructure—and temporary, targeted help for workers, small firms, and regions facing the biggest transition risks. Decisions should rely on transparent data, periodic review, and local participation so policies improve health and ecosystems without undermining competitiveness or basic affordability.
